main event: A UFO was sighted in Saint John, Canada on October 14, 1963, lasting for about 20 seconds.
interesting points: The object was described as self-luminous and having a familiar motion with the solar system., The report included various potential explanations for the sighting such as balloon, aircraft, or astronomical phenomenon., Accounts from witnesses indicated that multiple unidentified objects were sighted in the area., The sighting prompted a response from the U.S. Air Force, suggesting it might have been a satellite reentry., There were at least 30 unidentified objects sighted in the sky in the vicinity on October 9, 1963.
witness description: The witness felt confident that the sighting was genuine and distinct from known celestial objects.
